# Pokrovka, Kuganaksky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Pokrovka () is a rural locality (a selo) in Kuganaksky Selsoviet, Sterlitamaksky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 843 as of 2010.
Geography
It is located 30&nbsp;km from Sterlitamak, 7&nbsp;km from Bolshoy Kuganak.
